13:04.159 --> 13:05.393
Also, I want to build...

13:05.395 --> 13:08.262
But there were also
some bad times.

13:08.264 --> 13:09.564
Also some bad times.

13:09.566 --> 13:11.682
I mean, the point is,

13:11.684 --> 13:14.986
is that our relationship now
is just strictly business.

13:14.988 --> 13:17.588
Oh, speaking of which, we need
to upgrade the ventilation

13:17.590 --> 13:18.773
for the server farm.

13:18.775 --> 13:20.108
Oh, that's a good idea.

13:20.110 --> 13:21.993
Oh, also, I want to build
triple redundancy.

13:21.995 --> 13:24.278
Of course, but we shouldn't be
talking shop

13:24.280 --> 13:26.948
and leaving poor Zoey
out of the conversation.

13:26.950 --> 13:29.450
No, that's all right. I love
to hear about Walden's work.

13:29.452 --> 13:31.619
Oh, that's so sweet.

13:31.621 --> 13:34.705
I'm so glad
he found someone like you.

13:34.707 --> 13:37.091
Oh. Thank you.

13:37.093 --> 13:39.761
After I threw him out,
I wondered how he'd survive.

13:39.763 --> 13:40.995
He's so needy.

13:40.997 --> 13:42.380
I'm not needy.

13:42.382 --> 13:44.799
Yeah, you are.
BOTH: Yes, you are.

13:46.168 --> 13:47.301
So what's the deal?

13:47.303 --> 13:49.170
Are you guys in it
for the long haul,

13:49.172 --> 13:51.305
or are you just gonna date
and see what happens?

13:51.307 --> 13:54.358
Well, we're just finding
our way for the moment.

13:54.360 --> 13:55.860
(clears throat)
Oh, good.

13:55.862 --> 13:57.528
Mm.
Good.

13:57.530 --> 13:59.013
Keep it casual.

13:59.015 --> 14:01.315
That way no one can accuse you
of going after his money.

14:03.235 --> 14:04.585
Excuse me?

14:05.187 --> 14:07.288
I'm not after his money.

14:07.290 --> 14:09.490
Oh, no, you misunderstand.

14:09.492 --> 14:12.160
I... I'm sure you're not,
but unfortunately,

14:12.162 --> 14:13.911
there's no way to prove it.

14:15.214 --> 14:17.165
Luckily, I met him
when he had nothing,

14:17.167 --> 14:20.401
so there's no question
about my intentions.

14:20.403 --> 14:22.503
Are you questioning
my intentions?

14:22.505 --> 14:23.638
No, she's not. She's not.

14:23.640 --> 14:24.972
No, you're not.
You're not, are you?

14:24.974 --> 14:27.225
Of course not.

14:27.227 --> 14:29.010
Are <i>you</i> questioning
my intentions?

14:29.012 --> 14:31.712
Me? No!

14:35.150 --> 14:37.185
Berta, how is
the pot roast coming?

14:37.187 --> 14:39.070
Got another 30 minutes.

14:39.072 --> 14:40.888
You guys keep chatting.

14:42.991 --> 14:44.859
♪ Men. ♪

14:44.861 --> 14:46.360
I don't understand.

14:46.362 --> 14:49.063
Why is my grandmother
living with his grandmother?

14:49.065 --> 14:51.082
Yeah, I was kind of
wondering that myself,

14:51.084 --> 14:53.000
but I didn't want
to look stupid.

14:53.002 --> 14:54.952
Too late, dude.

14:54.954 --> 14:56.537
You want to handle this, Alan?

14:56.539 --> 14:57.538
Not really.

14:57.540 --> 14:59.257
I wasn't asking.

14:59.259 --> 15:01.075
All right. Um...

15:01.077 --> 15:04.128
Well, fellas, um,

15:04.130 --> 15:08.266
your two grandmas are,
uh... are both very lonely,

15:08.268 --> 15:13.137
and so, they've, uh, decided
to become...

15:13.139 --> 15:15.139
uh, roommates, uh,

15:15.141 --> 15:17.358
and keep each other company.

15:17.360 --> 15:18.559
Oh, that makes sense.
Mm.

15:18.561 --> 15:20.111
Plus, if one of them
falls down,

15:20.113 --> 15:21.529
the other can call
the ambulance.

15:21.531 --> 15:24.315
What if they both fall down
at the same time?

15:24.317 --> 15:26.734
Um, I guess they starve
to death and die.

15:26.736 --> 15:29.403
Unless they go cannibal
and try to eat each other.

15:29.405 --> 15:30.621
If that happens,
I'm betting

15:30.623 --> 15:32.940
on my grandma
eating your grandma.

15:32.942 --> 15:34.775
Dude, there's no way
in the world

15:34.777 --> 15:36.777
that your grandma
eats my grandma.

15:36.779 --> 15:39.247
My grandma totally
eats your grandma.

15:39.249 --> 15:42.583
Nuh-uh. If any grandma's doing
any eating, it's my grandma.

15:42.585 --> 15:44.168
ELDRIDGE: No way.
JAKE: Come on.

15:44.170 --> 15:46.137
My grandma has real teeth.
You happy?

15:46.139 --> 15:47.305
ELDRIDGE:
How do you know?

15:47.307 --> 15:49.223
JAKE:
She bit me once.

15:50.642 --> 15:52.176
Well, that was great.

15:52.178 --> 15:55.112
I'm really glad we got
to spend some time together.

15:55.114 --> 15:56.898
Yeah, it was lovely.

15:56.900 --> 15:58.482
Yeah. Oh, don't forget

15:58.484 --> 16:00.735
we have that meeting
with the venture fund tomorrow.

16:00.737 --> 16:01.903
Oh, yeah, right.

16:01.905 --> 16:03.971
Bye.
Oh, bye.

16:03.973 --> 16:05.773
Oh, do me a favor, Zoey.

16:05.775 --> 16:08.192
Don't let him wear sandals
to the meeting.

16:08.194 --> 16:10.027
I really don't tell him
what to wear.

16:10.029 --> 16:12.230
That's okay. You'll learn.

16:13.865 --> 16:15.533
Don't wear sandals
to the meeting.

16:15.535 --> 16:17.084
Good night.
Good night.

16:17.086 --> 16:18.419
Night-night.
Bye. Drive safe.

16:18.421 --> 16:20.871
Mm.

16:20.873 --> 16:22.623
(sighs)
I think that went great.

16:22.625 --> 16:23.958
Do you?

16:23.960 --> 16:25.459
You don't?

16:25.461 --> 16:26.711
I don't.

16:26.713 --> 16:28.963
I don't, either.

16:30.349 --> 16:32.850
Did... Um, did I miss something?

16:32.852 --> 16:35.186
Obviously,
you missed everything.

16:35.188 --> 16:36.771
That horrible woman
won't be happy

16:36.773 --> 16:38.472
till she's destroyed
our relationship,

16:38.474 --> 16:39.807
and she has you back.

16:39.809 --> 16:41.275
What? No!

16:41.277 --> 16:43.010
She has a boyfriend.
She's happy.

16:43.012 --> 16:45.846
Oh, how can you be so smart
about some things

16:45.848 --> 16:48.182
and so <i>stupid</i> about others?

16:48.184 --> 16:50.234
Okay, wait, just to be clear,

16:50.236 --> 16:53.520
what am I smart about
and what am I stupid about?!

16:55.173 --> 16:57.575
Oh, what?
Now you can't hear me!

16:57.577 --> 16:59.627
♪ Men. ♪

16:59.629 --> 17:02.163
Anybody want more
mashed potatoes?

17:02.165 --> 17:03.965
Oh, gosh, I'm
full, Jean,

17:03.967 --> 17:05.415
but everything's
so delicious.

17:05.417 --> 17:07.001
Thank you.

17:07.002 --> 17:09.837
And how lucky were you to
grow up with Mom's home cooking?

17:09.839 --> 17:12.306
Excuse me. You grew up
with home cooking, too.

17:12.308 --> 17:15.041
Yes, but the maid
did the cooking.

17:15.044 --> 17:17.345
It was still at home.

17:18.713 --> 17:21.214
Make sure
you leave room for dessert.

17:21.217 --> 17:22.650
I made pie.

17:22.652 --> 17:24.218
Oh, I love Grandma's pie.

17:25.654 --> 17:28.021
Yeah, yeah, I heard it, too.

17:28.023 --> 17:29.690
(clinking spoon on glass)

17:29.692 --> 17:32.326
There's something
I'd like to say.

17:32.328 --> 17:34.195
Oh, dear God, here it comes.

17:35.447 --> 17:40.034
It gives me such pleasure
to welcome Jean into my home

17:40.036 --> 17:43.788
and to share our new friendship
with our two families.

17:43.790 --> 17:46.040
Hear, hear.
Hear, hear.

17:46.042 --> 17:47.425
Hear, hear.

17:47.427 --> 17:50.544
And I'd just like to thank Evy
for showing me

17:50.546 --> 17:54.165
that it's never too late to
teach an old dog new tricks.

17:56.051 --> 17:58.752
Certainly didn't teach
her to fetch a bone.

17:58.754 --> 18:00.187
Shh.

18:01.589 --> 18:03.274
I have a question.

18:03.276 --> 18:05.176
Oh, God, here it comes.

18:06.194 --> 18:08.195
If you and her
were cannibals,

18:08.197 --> 18:10.981
which do you think
would eat the other?

18:13.985 --> 18:17.688
There you have it:
the upside of stupid.

18:22.110 --> 18:24.545
ZOEY: I'm sorry, Walden,
but Bridget's right.

18:24.547 --> 18:26.714
You have history with her;
you have none with me.

18:26.716 --> 18:28.716
You can't even be sure
I love you for yourself

18:28.718 --> 18:29.783
and not your money.

18:29.785 --> 18:30.968
What are you saying?

18:30.970 --> 18:32.803
I'm saying,
I think it might be better

18:32.805 --> 18:35.172
for both of us
if we went our separate ways.

18:35.174 --> 18:37.308
Okay, that's one approach...

18:37.310 --> 18:39.810
which stinks.

18:39.812 --> 18:43.314
So, let me make
a counterproposal.

18:43.316 --> 18:45.632
Why don't you move in with me?

18:45.634 --> 18:48.185
What?

18:48.187 --> 18:50.020
Yeah, you and Ava
move in with me.

18:50.022 --> 18:52.440
I love you,
and I want you in my life,

18:52.442 --> 18:54.859
I want... I want
to have a future with you.

18:54.861 --> 18:57.144
Really?

18:57.146 --> 18:58.496
Really.

18:58.498 --> 19:00.948
AVA: Mummy, Mummy,
please say yes!

19:00.950 --> 19:04.118
What are you doing
out of bed?!

19:04.120 --> 19:07.121
I love you, Walden!

19:07.123 --> 19:09.156
I love you, Ava.

19:09.158 --> 19:11.825
Get back into bed!

19:11.827 --> 19:13.127
Hmm. Let's see.

19:13.129 --> 19:16.514
So, that's one vote for yes,
and I vote yes,

19:16.516 --> 19:19.216
so, the motion is passed.

19:19.218 --> 19:22.603
There is one
tiny little problem.

19:22.605 --> 19:23.604
What's that?

19:23.606 --> 19:25.973
If Ava and I move in,

19:25.975 --> 19:29.844
isn't somebody going
to have to move out?

19:30.662 --> 19:33.447
Hmm.

19:34.699 --> 19:36.233
(groans)

19:36.235 --> 19:38.352
What's the matter?
I don't know.

19:38.354 --> 19:41.539
Just felt a little shiver
go down my spine.

19:41.541 --> 19:43.707
(groans)

